00:01:09.619 --> 00:01:13.180
unless the dealer also get a blackjack
in which case the hand is a push

00:01:13.180 --> 00:01:16.439
now let's look at how a hand of
blackjack plays out

00:01:16.439 --> 00:01:20.200
each hand begins with everyone getting
two cards

00:01:20.200 --> 00:01:23.820
all cards are dealt face-up except for
the dealers last card which is dealt

00:01:23.820 --> 00:01:24.630
face down

00:01:24.630 --> 00:01:28.439
the players all have to act first and
have four options

00:01:28.439 --> 00:01:32.490
hitting standing doubling down or
splitting a pair

00:01:32.490 --> 00:01:37.049
hitting means you want another card and in
blackjack you always use hand signals to

00:01:37.049 --> 00:01:38.619
tell the dealer what you want to do

00:01:38.619 --> 00:01:43.259
if you want to hit just tap the table in
front of your hand

00:01:43.259 --> 00:01:46.450
players can take as many cards as they
want until they either stand

00:01:46.450 --> 00:01:49.810
or go bust if you're happy with your
hand

00:01:49.810 --> 00:01:52.990
just wave your hand over your cards to
tell the dealer you stand

00:01:52.990 --> 00:01:57.049
on certain powerful hands you will want to
double down

00:01:57.049 --> 00:02:00.469
doubling down means you make a second
bet equal to your first

00:02:00.469 --> 00:02:04.909
and received one and only one more card
to tell the dealer you want to double down

00:02:04.909 --> 00:02:07.749
just place your second bet right next to
the first one

00:02:07.749 --> 00:02:10.770
if the players first two cards are a
pair

00:02:10.770 --> 00:02:13.970
they have the option of splitting them
and playing two separate hands

00:02:13.970 --> 00:02:18.220
to tell the dealer you want to split just
count out a second bet equal to your

00:02:18.220 --> 00:02:19.140
first in place a

00:02:19.140 --> 00:02:23.140
